{"data":{"projects":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"5G-NR ORAN ULPI","tech":["O-RAN","Massive MIMO","ULPI","7.2x Split","Open Fronthaul"],"github":null,"external":null,"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/6feaf5a1f2072fb8f6f5ee7cf5ba751f/346d7/oran.png","srcSet":"/static/6feaf5a1f2072fb8f6f5ee7cf5ba751f/eebcc/oran.png 300w,\n/static/6feaf5a1f2072fb8f6f5ee7cf5ba751f/0c107/oran.png 600w,\n/static/6feaf5a1f2072fb8f6f5ee7cf5ba751f/346d7/oran.png 1200w","sizes":"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/6feaf5a1f2072fb8f6f5ee7cf5ba751f/a22c2/oran.webp 300w,\n/static/6feaf5a1f2072fb8f6f5ee7cf5ba751f/300eb/oran.webp 600w,\n/static/6feaf5a1f2072fb8f6f5ee7cf5ba751f/a52e2/oran.webp 1200w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px, 100vw"}]},"width":1200,"height":800}}}},"html":"<p>ORAN ULPI (Uplink Performance Improvement) is a technology for Open RAN that boosts Massive MIMO efficiency. By utilizing the 7.2x (Cat-B) split, it moves complex beamforming tasks to the O-RU. This significantly slashes fronthaul data demands and costs while maintaining high-performance processing.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"5G-NR mmWave UE CPE/Modem (IAB)","tech":["5G NR","mmWave","IAB","3GPP","Backhaul"],"github":null,"external":null,"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/b6c4bf6d586ce49a841aec35e09adb20/346d7/IAB.png","srcSet":"/static/b6c4bf6d586ce49a841aec35e09adb20/eebcc/IAB.png 300w,\n/static/b6c4bf6d586ce49a841aec35e09adb20/0c107/IAB.png 600w,\n/static/b6c4bf6d586ce49a841aec35e09adb20/346d7/IAB.png 1200w","sizes":"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/b6c4bf6d586ce49a841aec35e09adb20/a22c2/IAB.webp 300w,\n/static/b6c4bf6d586ce49a841aec35e09adb20/300eb/IAB.webp 600w,\n/static/b6c4bf6d586ce49a841aec35e09adb20/a52e2/IAB.webp 1200w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px, 100vw"}]},"width":1200,"height":800}}}},"html":"<p>Integrated Access and Backhaul (IAB) enables 5G base stations to use wireless signals for both user connectivity and network backhaul. This eliminates the need for expensive fiber-optic cables at every site, making it faster and cheaper to expand 5G coverage, especially in dense urban areas.</p>"}}]}}}